Author: CryptoBeefy
Title: [TOKEN] ⋘Multibot⋙ Powerful multithreaded trading platform in the cloud
Body: I'm sad to see this ICO end. I've really gotten into the project and have been happy to promote it and also use the alpha. I've seen a few asking about how the bot did, so let me sum up my experience with it;  I tested with very low volume, about 1 LTC worth. I transferred 1 LTC from another exchange to Bittrex and then sold it there for tether (USD). I set up originally creating 20 orders between a 2% and 5% change. The problem with this is that LTC was quite stable during this period so I would only fulfil the first couple of orders but as it had created 20 orders, the buy in rate for the couple was only a 20th each of the LTC valuation. So, I decided to change it to only creating 5 orders still ranging between 2 and 5%. This then allowed me to maybe place all 5 but if price only allowed for a couple, more $'s would be invested as it wasn't split 20 ways.  Setting up was a piece a cake and any questions I did have were answered in a very quick timeframe. I requested in alpha to see a stats channel like the demo showed and this was added for me. The team seem to genuinely care which is nice to see.  I ran this one trade, USDT to LTC for 20 days and I sold some other altcoins during this period so had around $90 Multibot was able to use. After the 20 days I came away with around $110, so practically a dollar a day profit  Pros  So simple to use. Major exchange api capabilities. Seemed very robust. Helpful and supportive team. Lots of pairs to be able to trade.  Cons  You have no way of setting limits. E.g Do not buy above x and do not sell below y. I edited, stopped and restarted my project a number of times for various reasons and this messed up my stats page on that trade, I could only work out profit by exporting all my trades from Bittrex. No email alerts. I would like this to work in hand my limits points from above. It could send me an alert to say this was the price and it's then up to me whether I believe the price could go above or below that and decide whether to let the bot carry on or not.  I have raised the cons as a feature suggestion and have been told they're coming in the future so hopefully we see them introduced at some point. There are some other things i'd like to see like fancy graphs showing you what your most profitable trades were based upon date criteria you set etc etc but that isnt and wasnt necessary at this point but would be nice to see in a future version.

Author: cryptowatt
Title: [TOKEN] ⋘Multibot⋙ Powerful multithreaded trading platform in the cloud
Body: Hi there, Just a quick update on some of my experiences with Multibot. This is a great way to test in the crypto market space as stated multiple times you can have 5 threads in alpha. It seems to adjust to fluctuations in pricing via time since last trade or movement volume I am not sure yet but it has scared me when it has bought high. As a result I have stopped the bot multiple times and manually took over decreasing my profits. For example, I did not expect BCH to rise this much and was stunned when the bot was buying at over $600.... I realize now that is not the way to use this tool and it is best to set it up and let it run....if your worried about how much your potentially going to lose or gain you can set that in the individual thread under % or amount. By manually changing things I have lost out on profit so my earnings are off just because of my interference. The bot itself is extremely fast and well programed as I've bounced around the settings at mach 1 and there has not been any errors or stutters from that perspective. I will now be testing without messing with it this week and will update profits at that time. I currently have $1000 USD trading on 5 threads and only profited $50 which is not worth the risk of $1000 in market IMO. Again...I am at fault for these results by interfering. I just have a couple of suggestions, Adding money to the trades requires you to stop the bot and edit then restart it to accumulate new trades...or can I just edit it and after the bot completes it cycle it will readjust the new trades? also it is misspelled on site "stoped" should be "stopped" just a heads up. Devs are super responsive and very active on this site and on multibot.io which is encouraging to me. I think this project will succeed only as much as the effort that they put in so hats off guys. I will check back in once I've had a week of NOT TOUCHING MY BOT!

Author: A1ex
Title: [TOKEN] ⋘Multibot⋙ Powerful multithreaded trading platform in the cloud
Body: Announce ⋘ Alpha testing ⋙  A lot of people asked us to try something in our project. Trading bot is most interesting for everybody . We made free access to alpha version. Do you want to try it? Read rules and join us.  1. Alpha testing gives you 30 days access 2. We give access manualy (it will happen automatically in beta) by small parts. 3. You should be registred on multibot.io 4. Available 5 threads in alpha (It means you can start 5 tasks to trade on any exchange with any market). 5. Post your request here and provide your email address that are you using on multibot. 6. You must use bot, the accounts which aren't working will be turned off. 7. All questions about bot and how does it work must be here only. 8. For bug report use support in multibot. 9. You must post your feedback here. Negative or positive it doesn't matter. We will be glad to hear your opinion.  In this alpha we have opened only one strategy for poloniex, bitfinex, bittrex and wex (btce) exchanges.  How does it work?  This strategy works in cycle: 1. Placing Buy orders with a certain step between price to buy 2. Waiting when price will fall and checking orders 3. If one or more buy orders closed, it will calculate average price and will place sell order with specified percent for profit.   Be careful!  1. Use different api keys for each task. If some task stoped or deleted, you can use this api key again. 2. You can use one exchange account if you use different markets only. Balances for buying and selling must not cross. Example 1. You can trade on one account with markets BTC/USD, LTC/USD, ETH/USD and etc. Example 2. You can trade on one account with markets LTC/BTC, ETH/BTC, DASH/BTC and etc. Example 3. You can trade on one account with markets LTC/BTC, ETH/USD, DASH/USD. 3. Dont sell or buy anything on this account while trading bot is working. Or do this only if you understand very well how it works. 4. Dont turn on access in api for withdrawal. 5. There is not any form validation and etc. Check your setting before sending it.  How to start.  1. We recommend using balance no less than $100-200 or equivalent in crypto  2. Click to create a new task.    3. Choose settings.     4. Start it.    5. Wait profit

Author: A1ex
Title: [TOKEN] ⋘Multibot⋙ Powerful multithreaded trading platform in the cloud
Body: Website | Bounties | Whitepaper | Twitter | Youtube | Medium | Telegram | Facebook   Multibot ICO  October, 20 - November, 26      Multibot platform is aimed at solving the problem of user interaction with cryptocurrency exchanges and continuous monitoring of the market, at the maximum number of trading platforms. Based on and using the advantages of the SaaS model, the platform is designed to lower the threshold of entry into the exchange  trade  in  cryptocurrencies.  Automated  tools  that  do  not  require installation, with an intuitive interface and working 24/7 in the web -cloud will provide  protection  and  capital  turnover,  eliminate  manual  labor  and  take advantage of the volatility of the cryptocurrency for profit. Unlike other existing tools, it accumulates a maximum set of tools and services. The platform allows you to start using a few simple steps, regardless of the availability of hardware and other software, since it is available from anywhere in the world, with pre-defined settings and tools for successfully solving the main tasks.   What tools will Multibot develop for users?   Customizible analytics dashboard | Signals | Trading bot | Auto buy/sell tools | Arbitrage panel   How it works   The platform is based on various technologies for the implementation of all the tasks set, but the basis of the project is cloud technologies. The web-cloud allows you to quickly deploy any number of small isolated instances with a dedicated IP address, which is especially important for working with exchanges that limit the number of requests from one IP address. It is equally important to ensure the stable operation of the system as a whole, cloud technologies allow you to isolate web applications, providing full functionality for their operation.    Multibot platform blocksheme  Trading bot demo    Live demo is available. Please sign up.  Alpha testing announce!  Want to trying and testing our trading bot? Send your request for joining in our bitcointalk thread.  =https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=2248394.msg23507584#msg23507584  Proof-of-Work  The following PDF file contains 5 months of bot trading history for Ripple/USDT with $2000 deposit. You can verify any trade with historical market data.  https://multibot.io/xrp.pdf Caution: The size of this file is 22 Megabytes!   Multibot will work with all available crypto exchange markets    We are testing trading bot and signals now and In beta will available Poloniex, Bitfinex, Bittrex and Wex (BTC-e) markets.    Cloud technology   No instalation needed | Flexibility| Low cost of hardware | Work from any computer anywhere | Easy start     ICO structure   Multibot collects funds for the launch, promotion and development of the platform. For this purpose, Multibot (MBT) investment tokens, corresponding to the ERC20 standard, have been issued and are a smart contract based on the Ethereum platform. The platform will ensure the storage of collected funds and the disposal of them as necessary.      ICO detail   What is a Multibot token: Multibot token - represents the right to receive a part of company's profit. All token holders are eligible for obtaining dividends according to their stakes.
